---
import "../styles/article.css";

import fs from "node:fs";
import path from "node:path";
import Card from "../components/Card.astro";
import Icon from "../components/Icon.astro";
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";

// Read and parse the trade log CSV at build time
const csvPath = path.join(process.cwd(), "public/backtest/silver_alpha_trades_2023_2025.csv");
const csvRaw = fs.readFileSync(csvPath, "utf-8");
const lines = csvRaw.trim().split("\n");
const headers = lines[0].split(",");
const trades = lines.slice(1).map((line) => line.split(","));

// Compute stats
const returns = trades.map((t) => parseFloat(t[5]));
const wins = returns.filter((r) => r > 0).length;
const winRate = ((wins / returns.length) * 100).toFixed(1);
const avgReturn = (returns.reduce((a, b) => a + b, 0) / returns.length).toFixed(2);
const excessReturns = trades.map((t) => parseFloat(t[7]));
const avgExcess = (excessReturns.reduce((a, b) => a + b, 0) / excessReturns.length).toFixed(2);
const avgDays = Math.round(trades.reduce((a, t) => a + parseInt(t[8]), 0) / trades.length);

// Column display names
const colNames: Record<string, string> = {
	symbol: "Symbol",
	entry_date: "Entry",
	exit_date: "Exit",
	entry_price: "Entry $",
	exit_price: "Exit $",
	return_pct: "Return %",
	spy_return_pct: "SPY %",
	excess_pct: "Excess %",
	days_held: "Days",
	exit_reason: "Exit Reason",
};
---

<Layout
	title="Silver Alpha Strategy"
	description="Systematic swing trade strategy: 94 trades, 62% win rate, +325% return — full trade log transparency."
>
	<div class="left" slot="left">
		<Card class="toc-card">
			<h2 class="no-mt">On this page</h2>
			<ol>
				<li class="toc-li"><a href="#_top" class="active">Overview</a></li>
				<li class="toc-li"><a href="#oos-definition">Out-of-Sample Definition</a></li>
				<li class="toc-li"><a href="#performance">Performance</a></li>
				<li class="toc-li"><a href="#equity-curve">Equity Curve</a></li>
				<li class="toc-li"><a href="#disclosures">What's Not Shown</a></li>
				<li class="toc-li"><a href="#trade-log">Trade Log</a></li>
			</ol>
		</Card>
	</div>
	<article slot="right" data-pagefind-body>
		<Card>
			<h1 class="no-mt" id="_top" style="scroll-margin-top: 2rem;">Silver Alpha Strategy</h1>
			<p style="color: #c7c7c7; margin-top: 0.5rem;">
				Systematic swing trade strategy — 2023 to Q1 2026 out-of-sample simulation.
			</p>

			<p>
				Silver Alpha is a swing trade strategy built on Aerondight's multi-factor scoring engine.
				It uses conviction scores and signal transitions to systematically enter and exit positions
				in US equities. All decisions are fully systematic — no discretionary overrides.
			</p>

			<h2 id="oos-definition" style="scroll-margin-top: 4rem;">Out-of-Sample Definition</h2>

			<p>
				The scoring models were trained on data through December 31, 2022, and fully locked as of that date.
				The Silver Alpha simulation runs from January 2023 through March 2026 — meaning every trade shown
				uses signals generated from a frozen model on data it had never seen during training. No hyperparameters,
				features, or weights were modified during the simulation window.
			</p>

			<h2 id="performance" style="scroll-margin-top: 4rem;">Performance</h2>

			<div class="stats-grid">
				<div class="stat-card">
					<span class="stat-value">{trades.length}</span>
					<span class="stat-label">Total Trades</span>
				</div>
				<div class="stat-card">
					<span class="stat-value">{winRate}%</span>
					<span class="stat-label">Win Rate</span>
				</div>
				<div class="stat-card">
					<span class="stat-value">{avgReturn}%</span>
					<span class="stat-label">Avg Return</span>
				</div>
				<div class="stat-card">
					<span class="stat-value">{avgExcess}%</span>
					<span class="stat-label">Avg Excess vs SPY</span>
				</div>
				<div class="stat-card">
					<span class="stat-value">{avgDays}d</span>
					<span class="stat-label">Avg Holding Period</span>
				</div>
				<div class="stat-card">
					<span class="stat-value">2.07</span>
					<span class="stat-label">Sharpe (vs SPY 1.44)</span>
				</div>
				<div class="stat-card">
					<span class="stat-value">-26.49%</span>
					<span class="stat-label">Max Drawdown</span>
				</div>
			</div>

			<p>
				<img src="/backtest/performance_summary.png" alt="Performance summary with signal quality and portfolio statistics" style="max-width: 100%;" />
			</p>

			<h2 id="equity-curve" style="scroll-margin-top: 4rem;">Equity Curve</h2>

			<p>Silver Alpha vs SPY buy-and-hold over the simulation period:</p>

			<p>
				<img src="/backtest/silver_alpha_equity_curve.png" alt="Silver Alpha equity curve vs SPY" style="max-width: 100%;" />
			</p>

			<p>
				<img src="/backtest/quintile_returns.png" alt="Quintile returns showing monotonic Q1-Q5 separation" style="max-width: 100%;" />
			</p>

			<h2 id="disclosures" style="scroll-margin-top: 4rem;">What's Not Shown</h2>

			<div class="disclosure-section">
				<p>
					<strong>Portfolio simulation methodology.</strong> The equity curve reflects a 10-bucket portfolio:
					up to 10 concurrent positions, each bucket independently holds either a single stock or SPY.
					When a stock triggers a SELL signal, the bucket rotates into SPY; when a new BUY signal appears,
					the bucket sells SPY and buys the stock. This keeps capital fully deployed at all times and
					provides a clean benchmark-relative comparison.
				</p>
				<p>
					<strong>Survivorship bias (partial).</strong> The ~900-name universe is composed of current
					S&amp;P 500 and S&amp;P 400 MidCap members, refreshed annually at year-end. Intra-year index
					changes are not reflected, meaning a stock added or removed mid-year could introduce minor
					survivorship effects. I've manually removed some of the most obvious cases, but the log still
					carries some residual bias. Future versions will use point-in-time index membership.
				</p>
				<p>
					<strong>Fundamental data is point-in-time.</strong> All fundamental inputs to the scoring engine
					use as-of-record-date values — no look-ahead bias. A trade on 2024-03-15 only sees fundamentals
					filed before that date.
				</p>
				<p>
					<strong>What's still not modeled:</strong> slippage, transaction costs, borrow costs for any
					short exposure, and realistic market-impact assumptions. The simulation reflects signal quality
					at execution, not a fully deployed portfolio's net returns.
				</p>
			</div>

			<h2 id="trade-log" style="scroll-margin-top: 4rem;">Trade Log</h2>

			<p>
				Every trade is logged with full transparency. {trades.length} completed trades from January 2023 through Q1 2026.
				<a href="/backtest/silver_alpha_trades_2023_2025.csv" style="margin-left: 0.5rem;">Download CSV</a>
			</p>

			<div class="table-wrapper">
				<table>
					<thead>
						<tr>
							{headers.map((h) => <th>{colNames[h] || h}</th>)}
						</tr>
					</thead>
					<tbody>
						{trades.map((row) => (
							<tr>
								{row.map((cell, i) => (
									<td class:list={{
										positive: headers[i] === "return_pct" && parseFloat(cell) > 0,
										negative: headers[i] === "return_pct" && parseFloat(cell) < 0,
										"excess-positive": headers[i] === "excess_pct" && parseFloat(cell) > 0,
										"excess-negative": headers[i] === "excess_pct" && parseFloat(cell) < 0,
									}}>
										{headers[i] === "return_pct" || headers[i] === "spy_return_pct" || headers[i] === "excess_pct"
											? `${parseFloat(cell).toFixed(2)}%`
											: headers[i] === "entry_price" || headers[i] === "exit_price"
												? `$${parseFloat(cell).toFixed(2)}`
												: headers[i] === "symbol"
													? cell.replace(".US", "")
													: cell}
									</td>
								))}
							</tr>
						))}
					</tbody>
				</table>
			</div>
		</Card>
	</article>
</Layout>
<script src="../scripts/toc.ts"></script>
<style>
	.disclosure-section {
		border: 1px solid #353535;
		padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem;
		margin: 1rem 0 1.5rem;
		font-size: 0.925rem;
		line-height: 1.6;
		color: #c7c7c7;
	}

	.disclosure-section p:first-child {
		margin-top: 0;
	}

	.disclosure-section p:last-child {
		margin-bottom: 0;
	}

	.disclosure-section strong {
		color: #ffffff;
	}

	.stats-grid {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: repeat(5, 1fr);
		gap: 1rem;
		margin: 1.5rem 0;
	}

	@media screen and (max-width: 900px) {
		.stats-grid {
			grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
		}
	}

	@media screen and (max-width: 640px) {
		.stats-grid {
			grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
		}
	}

	.stat-card {
		border: 1px solid #353535;
		padding: 1rem;
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		align-items: center;
		text-align: center;
	}

	.stat-value {
		font-size: 1.5em;
		font-weight: 700;
		font-family: 'Geist Mono', 'Courier New', Courier, monospace;
		color: var(--primary-light);
	}

	.stat-label {
		font-size: 0.8rem;
		color: #c7c7c7;
		margin-top: 0.25rem;
	}

	.table-wrapper {
		overflow-x: auto;
		margin-top: 1rem;
		border: 1px solid #353535;
	}

	.table-wrapper table {
		margin: 0;
		width: 100%;
		font-size: 0.825rem;
		font-family: 'Geist Mono', 'Courier New', Courier, monospace;
		white-space: nowrap;
	}

	.table-wrapper th {
		background: #1a1a1a;
		padding: 0.5rem 0.75rem;
		font-size: 0.75rem;
		text-transform: uppercase;
		letter-spacing: 0.05em;
		color: #c7c7c7;
		position: sticky;
		top: 0;
	}

	.table-wrapper td {
		padding: 0.4rem 0.75rem;
	}

	.table-wrapper tbody tr:hover {
		background: rgba(140, 92, 245, 0.08);
	}

	.positive { color: #16c79a; }
	.negative { color: #e94560; }
	.excess-positive { color: #16c79a; }
	.excess-negative { color: #e94560; }
</style>
